Methods.S:
The tracer was ejected electrophoretically (10-20 pA, 4 
    seconds on14 seconds off, or 8 seconds on18 seconds off; 10-20 FA; 
    10-20 minutes), and left there 10-20 minutes before withdrawal.

Discussion.S:
Several cells in these nuclei project to the SC in the 
    ipsilateral side in the rat (Killackey and Erzurumlu, '81; 
    Huerta et al., '83; Bruce et al., '87).

Commands generated in the SC are transferred through the 
    PDB to the motor control systems of the eye, head, and body (Otani 
    et al., '81; Hess, '82; Swenson and Castro, '83; 
    Huerta and Harting, '84b; Chevalier and Deniau, '84; 
    Redgrave et al., '86, '87; Bickford and Hall, '89) 
    in the squirrel (May and Hall, '841, the rabbit (Holstege and 
    Collewijin, '82), the cat (Weber et al., '78; Saint-Cyr 
    and Courville, '81, '82; Grantyn and Grantyn, '82; 
    Jeneskog, '83; McIlwain, '861, and the primate 
    (Raczkowski et al., '76; Harting, '77).
